<h1>Inner Planets</h1>
<p>The inner planets are Mercury, Venus, Earth, and Mars. These planets are closest to the Sun and have rocky surfaces.</p>

<h2>Mercury</h2>
<p>Mercury is the closest planet to the Sun and the smallest planet in the solar system.</p>

<h2>Venus</h2>
<p>Venus has a thick atmosphere and is the hottest planet in the solar system.</p>

<h2>Earth</h2>
<p>Earth is our home planet and the only known planet with life.</p>

<h2>Mars</h2>
<p>Mars is called the Red Planet and is a major focus of future exploration.</p>

